# InterviewMe — Ultimate Backend Engineering Plan

> A phased, production-grade backend engineering blueprint for building an AI-powered mock interview platform on a $0 budget. This document is your roadmap — every module, every endpoint, every design decision is documented before a single line of code is written.

---

## Stack Summary (Locked In)

| Layer | Technology | Why |
|-------|-----------|-----|
| **Runtime** | Python 3.12 + FastAPI | Async-native, WebSocket support, type hints |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (Heroku) | Relational, JSONB support, battle-tested |
| **ORM** | SQLAlchemy 2.0 + Alembic | Async support, migrations |
| **LLM** | Groq API (Llama 3.3 70B) | Free tier, ~200ms first-token, streaming |
| **Auth** | JWT-based (issued by NextAuth.js on frontend) | Stateless, simple validation on backend |
| **WebSocket** | FastAPI native WebSocket | Real-time interview sessions |
| **Hosting** | Heroku (GitHub Student Pack) | No cold starts, Postgres included |
| **Caching** | In-memory (dict) for MVP → Redis later | Keep it simple |

