## Phase 2: CV/JD Processing & Interview Creation

> **Goal:** Users can upload a CV and job description, the backend processes them with the LLM, and creates a ready-to-start interview session.

### 2.1 — Text Extraction

**What:** Extract text from uploaded files (PDF, DOCX) or accept raw pasted text.

**Supported inputs:**
| Format | Library | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| PDF | `PyPDF2` or `pdfplumber` | `pdfplumber` handles tables better |
| DOCX | `python-docx` | Standard library |
| Plain text | None | Direct pass-through |

**`app/utils/text_extraction.py`:**
- `extract_text(file: UploadFile) -> str` — Auto-detects format, extracts text
- Validates file size (max 5MB), file type, and extracted content length
- Raises `ValidationError` if CV is empty or unreadable

---

### 2.2 — CV Analysis (LLM Processing)

**What:** Take raw CV text and extract structured data using Groq.

**`app/modules/ai/cv_processor.py`:**

**Input:** Raw CV text (string)

**Output:** Structured JSON:
```json
{
    "candidate_name": "...",
    "years_of_experience": 3,
    "current_role": "Junior Software Engineer",
    "skills": {
        "technical": ["Python", "React", "PostgreSQL"],
        "soft": ["communication", "teamwork"]
    },
    "experience": [
        {
            "role": "Software Engineer",
            "company": "Acme Corp",
            "duration": "2 years",
            "key_achievements": ["Led migration to microservices", "..."]
        }
    ],
    "education": [...],
    "projects": [...],
    "notable_points": ["Published research paper on ML", "..."],
    "potential_gaps": ["No cloud experience mentioned", "..."]
}
```

**Why structured?** This goes into `interview.cv_analysis` (JSONB column) and gets injected into interview prompts. Structured = queryable + smaller token footprint per turn.

**Token budget:** ~500-800 tokens for the system prompt + raw CV, ~300-400 tokens for the response. One Groq call, no streaming needed here (it's a preprocessing step).

---

### 2.3 — JD Analysis (LLM Processing)

**`app/modules/ai/jd_processor.py`:**

**Input:** Raw job description text

**Output:** Structured JSON:
```json
{
    "role_title": "Senior Backend Engineer",
    "company": "Tech Corp",
    "seniority_level": "senior",
    "required_skills": ["Python", "System Design", "AWS"],
    "nice_to_have": ["Kubernetes", "GraphQL"],
    "key_responsibilities": ["Design APIs", "Mentor juniors"],
    "interview_focus_areas": ["system design", "leadership", "Python deep dive"],
    "culture_signals": ["fast-paced", "startup", "remote-first"]
}
```

---

### 2.4 — Interview Creation Endpoint

**`app/modules/interviews/router.py`:**

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `POST` | `/api/interviews` | Create new interview |
| `GET` | `/api/interviews` | List user's interviews |
| `GET` | `/api/interviews/{id}` | Get interview details |
| `DELETE` | `/api/interviews/{id}` | Delete interview + related data |

**Create interview flow:**

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["POST /api/interviews
    {cv_file, jd_text}"] --> B[Extract text from CV]
    B --> C[Validate: CV has content]
    C --> D["Create Interview record
    status=PROCESSING_CV"]
    D --> E[LLM: Analyze CV → structured JSON]
    E --> F[LLM: Analyze JD → structured JSON]
    F --> G[LLM: Generate gap analysis + focus areas]
    G --> H["Update interview:
    cv_analysis, jd_analysis
    status=READY"]
    H --> I["Return interview object
    {id, status, target_role}"]
```

**Design decision — Sync vs Async processing:**

For MVP, process CV/JD **synchronously** in the POST request. The full pipeline takes ~3-5 seconds on Groq (it's fast). This keeps the architecture simple. For scale, you'd move this to a background task (Celery) and poll for status.

If Groq takes longer than expected, set a **15-second timeout** and return status `PROCESSING_CV` so the frontend can poll.

---

### Phase 2 Deliverable Checklist
- [ ] File upload endpoint accepts PDF, DOCX, plain text
- [ ] Text extraction works for all formats
- [ ] CV analysis returns consistent structured JSON from Groq
- [ ] JD analysis returns consistent structured JSON from Groq
- [ ] Interview record created with status transitions
- [ ] List/get/delete endpoints work with auth
- [ ] Error handling for: bad files, Groq failures, empty content

